Class AbstractAttributeIndex<A,O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.cqengine.index.common.AbstractAttributeIndex<A,O>
  • Type Parameters:
    A - The type of the attribute on which this index will be built
    O - The type of the object containing the attribute
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ModificationListener<O>, AttributeIndex<A,O>, Index<O>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractMapBasedAttributeIndex, InvertedRadixTreeIndex, RadixTreeIndex, ReversedRadixTreeIndex, SuffixTreeIndex, UniqueIndex

    public abstract class AbstractAttributeIndex<A,O>
extends Object
implements AttributeIndex<A,O>
    A skeleton implementation of an index which implements the Index.supportsQuery(Query) method, based on a set of queries supported by a subclass supplied to the constructor.
    Author:
    Niall Gallagher
